The paper discusses the evaluation and testing of deep learning models, which falls under the domain of software engineering (cs.SE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed system is based on dataset characterization, which involves analyzing the properties of the dataset, such as equivalence partitioning, centroid positioning, boundary conditioning, and pair-wise boundary conditioning. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of deep learning models in safety-critical applications, which may relate to the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category.
